This paper deals with the analysis of differential privacy for learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the privacy amplification by iteration technique, which is commonly used in machine learning and optimization algorithms, and thus it is likely to also fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information theory (cs.IT), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
